Fetch mRNA and CDS information from GFF3 files. For example:

  ./bin/gff3-fetch mrna test/data/gff/test.gff3
  ./bin/gff3-fetch cds test/data/gff/test.gff3

This implementation depends on BioRuby's GFF3 parser, with the possible
advantage that it does not consume all memory. You can use it as a BioRuby
plugin by adding the 'lib' dir to the search path and

  require 'bio/db/gff/gffdb'

For a writeup see http://thebird.nl/bioruby/BioRuby_GFF3.html 

Pjotr Prins
